The paper deals with unsupervised representation learning from images using auto-encoder architectures. This topic is primarily related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the role of network depth and capacity, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the models based on their feature spaces, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
